node.title: Northern Territory records one new COVID-19 case
node.alt: Michael Gunner at COVID press conference wearing a mask on November 18, 2021.
node.description: The Chief Minister says the Northern Territory recorded one new case of coronavirus.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded one new case of coronavirus, according to the Chief Minister.", "The new case is a 31-year-old fully vaccinated woman from Robinson River.", "The woman, a close contact of a previous case, was transferred to Howard Springs on Wednesday and tested positive in quarantine.", "She was not infectious while in Robinson\u00a0River, Chief Minister Michael Gunner said.", "He said no new exposure sites had\u00a0been added.", "The full list of all current NT public exposure sites\u00a0can be found on the NT government's coronavirus\u00a0website.", "Earlier today Mr Gunner announced that the\u00a0Territory-wide mask mandate would lift\u00a0at 11am this morning.", "But a mask mandate remains in place in the locked-down areas of\u00a0Katherine and Robinson River.", "There were 3,083 tests undertaken in the NT in 24 hours.", "Of those, 512 were recorded in Katherine and 230 in the nearby remote community of Binjari.", "Yesterday Mr Gunner said a positive wastewater sample had been\u00a0detected in Binjari, which falls within the Katherine lockdown area.", "Today he said every resident in Binjari, who had been\u00a0anxiously awaiting\u00a0today's results,\u00a0had been tested overnight.", "Mr Gunner said additional wastewater testing in Binjari, however, had returned a stronger positive result.", "The results mean authorities are expecting to find at least one positive case in Binjari, Mr Gunner said.", "More to come."]
